to the editor your dec 29 front page article at odds with harvard president black studies stars eye princeton was correct in describing lawrence h summers the president of harvard as proud of harvard 's afro american studies department collectively and individually and anxious to compete vigorously to make this an attractive environment but the article left the impression that prof cornel west had not been productive in recent years this is clearly not the case since 1998 dr west has produced at least four books including one about how black americans shaped this country one on the future of american progressivism a critical reader and one about america 's beleaguered parents alan j stone vice president government community and public affairs harvard university cambridge mass jan 2 2002

